us how many were missed (False Negatives). The Classification Report provides the final Precision, Recall, and F1-Score.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\nprint(\"Running predictions on the Test set\")\n# 1. On demande au modèle de prédire les probabilités (entre 0 et 1)\npredictions = model.predict(test_generator)\n\n# 2. On transforme les probabilités en choix fermés (> 50% = Malade)\ny_pred = (predictions > 0.5).astype(int).reshape(-1)\n\n# 3. On récupère les vraies réponses depuis le générateur\ny_true = test_generator.classes\n\n# 4. On dessine la Matrice\ncm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)\nplt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\nsns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', \n            xticklabels=['Healthy (0)', 'Sick (1)'], \n            yticklabels=['Healthy (0)', 'Sick (1)'])\nplt.title('Final Confusion Matrix: Healthy vs Sick')\nplt.xlabel('Predicted Label')\nplt.ylabel('True Label')\nplt.show()\n\nprint(\"\\nFinal Classification Report:\\n\")\nprint(classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=['Healthy', 'Sick']))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-11T14:23:20.554243Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-11T14:23:20.554999Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.224146Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-11T14:23:20.554974Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.223467Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Running predictions on the Test set\n\u001b[1m241/241\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m25s\u001b[0m 78ms/step\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x600 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"\nFinal Classification Report:\n\n              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n\n     Healthy       0.51      0.96      0.67      3843\n        Sick       0.69      0.08      0.15      3843\n\n    accuracy                           0.52      7686\n   macro avg       0.60      0.52      0.41      7686\nweighted avg       0.60      0.52      0.41      7686\n\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.3. Prediction Confidence Analysis\nUse a boxplot to visualize the distribution of the predicted probabilities. This shows how \"confident\" the model is. A clear separation between the probabilities assigned to True Healthy patients and True Sick patients indicates a highly discriminative model.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\nprint(\"Generating Prediction Probability Boxplot\")\n\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame({\n    'True Label': ['Sick' if label == 1 else 'Healthy' for label in y_true],\n    'Predicted Probability of being Sick': predictions.reshape(-1)\n})\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\nsns.boxplot(data=results_df, x='True Label', y='Predicted Probability of being Sick', palette='Set2')\nplt.axhline(0.5, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Decision Threshold (50%)')\nplt.title('Boxplot of Model Confidence (Probabilities)')\nplt.legend()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.225047Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.225386Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.410901Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.225360Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.410085Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Generating Prediction Probability Boxplot\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"/tmp/ipykernel_55/2020331740.py:9: FutureWarning: \n\nPassing `palette` without assigning `hue` is deprecated and will be removed in v0.14.0. Assign the `x` variable to `hue` and set `legend=False` for the same effect.\n\n  sns.boxplot(data=results_df, x='True Label', y='Predicted Probability of being Sick', palette='Set2')\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x600 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Phase 2 of Hierarchical Approach: Diagnosing the Stage\nBuilding of the second model. This model will only look at the \"Sick\" patients and classify them into 3 stages: Very Mild, Mild, and Moderate Demented.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Preparing balanced dataset for Phase 2 (Sick patients only)\")\n\nsick_filepaths = []\nsick_labels = []\n\ntarget_folders = ['very mild dementia', 'mild dementia', 'moderate dementia']\n\nfor folder in os.listdir(data_dir):\n    if folder.lower() in target_folders: \n        folder_path = os.path.join(data_dir, folder)\n        if os.path.isdir(folder_path):\n            for file in os.listdir(folder_path):\n                if file.endswith('.jpg'):\n                    sick_filepaths.append(os.path.join(folder_path, file))\n                    sick_labels.append(folder)\n\nsick_df = pd.DataFrame({'path': sick_filepaths, 'label': sick_labels})\n\n\n\nmin_count = sick_df['label'].value_counts().min()\nprint(f\"The smallest class has {min_count} images. Downsampling all classes to {min_count}...\")\n\n\nbalanced_sick_df = sick_df.groupby('label').sample(n=min_count, random_state=42)\n\n\nbalanced_sick_df = balanced_sick_df.sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ntrain_sick_df, test_sick_df = train_test_split(balanced_sick_df, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=balanced_sick_df['label'])\n\nprint(f\"Phase 2 Dataset ready: {len(balanced_sick_df)} total sick images.\")\nprint(\"\\nLabel distribution in Training Set:\")\nprint(train_sick_df['label'].value_counts())\n\n# Data Generators\ntrain_gen_sick = datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n    dataframe=train_sick_df, x_col='path', y_col='label',\n    target_size=(128, 128), batch_size=32, class_mode='categorical', validate_filenames=False\n)\n\ntest_gen_sick = datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n    dataframe=test_sick_df, x_col='path', y_col='label',\n    target_size=(128, 128), batch_size=32, class_mode='categorical', shuffle=False, validate_filenames=False\n)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.412012Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.412352Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.469176Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.412328Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.468576Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Preparing balanced dataset for Phase 2 (Sick patients only)\nThe smallest class has 488 images. Downsampling all classes to 488...\nPhase 2 Dataset ready: 1464 total sick images.\n\nLabel distribution in Training Set:\nlabel\nMild Dementia         391\nVery mild Dementia    390\nModerate Dementia     390\nName: count, dtype: int64\nFound 1171 non-validated image filenames belonging to 3 classes.\nFound 293 non-validated image filenames belonging to 3 classes.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":9},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\nbase_model_2 = EfficientNetB0(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(128, 128, 3))\nbase_model_2.trainable = True\nfor layer in base_model_2.layers[:-20]: \n    layer.trainable = False\n\nmodel_stage = Sequential([\n    base_model_2,\n    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),\n    BatchNormalization(),\n    Dropout(0.5),\n    Dense(3, activation='softmax') \n])\n\nmodel_stage.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=1e-4),\n              loss='categorical_crossentropy', \n              metrics=['accuracy'])\n\nprint(\"Training for Phase 2 on balanced data\")\n\nhistory_stage = model_stage.fit(\n    train_gen_sick,\n    epochs=15, # J'ai mis 15 epochs car le dataset est petit, il a besoin de plus de tours pour apprendre\n    validation_data=test_gen_sick,\n    callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=4, restore_best_weights=True)]\n)\n\nprint(\"Phase 2 Training complete\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.470089Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-11T14:23:46.470407Z","iopub.status.idle":